 *   how to write a C++ client that connects to this server and
 *   exchanges `NetworkMessage` frames. Runnable loopback example
 *   in `examples/11_client.cpp`.
 * - @ref tutorial_result_errors â€” Every network call returns
 *   `GameResult<T>`.
 * - @ref tutorial_foundation_adapters â€” Register
 *   `GameNetworkManager` in a `ServiceLocator` for DI access.
 * - @ref tutorial_spatial_world â€” Interest management reduces
 *   broadcast traffic on large worlds.
 * - `advanced/PROTOCOL_SPECIFICATION.md` â€” Authoritative list
 *   of opcode ranges and payload layouts used by the built-in
 *   microservices.
 * - `include/cgs/foundation/game_network_manager.hpp` â€”
 *   authoritative API.
 * - `include/cgs/foundation/signal.hpp` â€” generic `Signal<T>`.
 */
